                </div>
                <div id="question3" class="collapse show" style="">
                    <div class="card-body"> GORM is Grails' object relational mapping (ORM) implementation. Under the hood it uses Hibernate (a very popular and flexible open source ORM solution) and thanks to the dynamic nature of Groovy with its static and dynamic typing, along with the convention of Grails, there is far less configuration involved in creating Grails domain classes. </div>
                </div>
            </div>
